<plot>This short shows how Hollywood gets ready for the world premiere of an "important" movie. The film celebrated here is _Marie Antoinette (1938)_ (qv), which had its premiere at the Carthay Circle Theatre. We see the street leading to the theatre transformed to suggest a garden that might be seen in a French palace. This includes the placement of trees and other foliage, as well as large statues along the route. Grandstands are set up so fans can see their favorite stars as they arrive for the premiere. Finally, the proverbial "galaxy of stars" arrives in their limousines. 'Fanny Brice' (qv) and 'Pete Smith (I)' (qv) make remarks at the microphone set up on the carpet outside the theatre.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?243242</url></doc>
